# Conquest Design Law

Conquest UI is a **Digital Command Center**, not a SaaS analytics dashboard.

Read [`docs/design/design-architecture-constitution.md`](docs/design/design-architecture-constitution.md) before any UI work.

## Four layers (required shell)

1. **Command Layer** — search, AI command bar, model switcher (always visible)
2. **Navigation Rail** — modules, not pages
3. **Module Workspace** — independent environment per module
4. **Intelligence Dock** — always-alive right panel

## Forbidden

- Generic sidebar + cards + charts layout
- Static KPI tiles without drill-down, confidence, prediction
- Feature boxes instead of Intelligence Models
- Chat-only UI without command layer
- Decorative animation

## Required

- Smart Summary Cards (value, deltas, insight, confidence, prediction)
- Intelligence Models transform workspace (Growth, Commerce, Social, etc.)
- Hover intelligence on primary visualizations
- Full drill-down expansion (metric → platform → segment → revenue)
- Motion 150–250ms for state only

## Principle

Reduce visual complexity. Increase information density.
